            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer to make it impossible for other men to approach a certain woman. Three words from the incipit, which are taken 
                    from <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1978BritishLibrary"/><citedRange unit="page">147</citedRange></bibl> are certainly
                    ʾasmāt. Two of them are derived from Islamic Arabic formulas, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ar">lā ʾilah ʾilla ʾAllāh</foreign> and 
                    <foreign xml:lang="ar">bi-smi-llāh</foreign>. The third is possibly related to Mount Carmel in the Holy land, as it is mentioned
                    for instance in <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1672Isaiah"/>.</p>
            </abstract>
